‚∏ª

1. XGBoost Regression
	‚Ä¢	Overview: An ensemble learning method that utilizes gradient boosting of decision trees, known for its speed and performance.
	‚Ä¢	Strengths:
	‚Ä¢	High accuracy and efficiency on structured/tabular data.
	‚Ä¢	Robust handling of missing data and outliers.
	‚Ä¢	Widely adopted in industry for tasks like demand forecasting and risk assessment.
	‚Ä¢	Use Cases: Finance, healthcare, and supply chain analytics.

‚∏ª

2. CatBoost Regression
	‚Ä¢	Overview: A gradient boosting algorithm developed by Yandex, designed to handle categorical features effectively.
	‚Ä¢	Strengths:
	‚Ä¢	Efficient processing of categorical variables without extensive preprocessing.
	‚Ä¢	Competitive performance with minimal parameter tuning.
	‚Ä¢	Strong generalization capabilities.
	‚Ä¢	Use Cases: Customer behavior prediction, recommendation systems, and financial modeling.

‚∏ª

3. Deep Regression Models with Test-Time Adaptation
	‚Ä¢	Overview: Advanced neural network-based regression models that adapt to new data distributions during inference.
	‚Ä¢	Strengths:
	‚Ä¢	Ability to adjust to environmental changes in real-time.
	‚Ä¢	Enhanced performance in dynamic and non-stationary settings.
	‚Ä¢	Suitable for complex, high-dimensional data. Ôøº
