XGBoost is considered one of the best regression models for structured data because it strikes a powerful balance between accuracy, speed, and flexibility. Here‚Äôs why it‚Äôs preferred over many others:

‚∏ª

1. High Predictive Accuracy
	‚Ä¢	Uses gradient boosting, which builds trees iteratively and corrects errors from previous ones.
	‚Ä¢	Often wins machine learning competitions (e.g., Kaggle) due to its top-notch performance.

2. Handles Real-World Data Well
	‚Ä¢	Supports missing values, noisy data, and non-linear relationships better than linear models.
	‚Ä¢	Automatically captures interactions between features.

3. Fast and Scalable
	‚Ä¢	Uses parallel tree boosting and optimized memory usage.
	‚Ä¢	Can process large datasets much faster than traditional models like Random Forest or deep learning (on tabular data).

4. Fine Control Over Model Behavior
	‚Ä¢	Provides many hyperparameters (like learning rate, max depth, etc.) to control underfitting/overfitting precisely.

5. Feature Importance & Interpretability
	‚Ä¢	Outputs feature importance scores, which helps explain model predictions‚Äîuseful in regulated industries like finance or healthcare.


