üßæ Problem Statement

In many regions, users often travel to nearby ATMs expecting to withdraw cash, only to discover that the ATM is either out of service, lacks sufficient funds, or does not dispense the required denominations. This causes user inconvenience, wasted time, and unnecessary travel, especially in densely populated or cash-dependent areas. There is currently no accurate, real-time system that predicts ATM cash availability and denomination breakdown before the user arrives.

The goal is to build an intelligent, adaptive system that can:
	‚Ä¢	Predict the likelihood of cash availability at nearby ATMs.
	‚Ä¢	Estimate denomination availability (e.g., ‚Çπ100, ‚Çπ500, ‚Çπ2000).
	‚Ä¢	Adapt to location, time, and user withdrawal patterns using AI/ML models.


Here is a technical solution description, clearly structured for your idea:

‚∏ª

üõ†Ô∏è Technical Solution

This system uses a combination of XGBoost regression and Ball Tree spatial search to provide real-time ATM cash and denomination availability to users based on their location and withdrawal needs.

üîπ Step-by-Step Architecture:
	1.	User Input
	‚Ä¢	User enters the required withdrawal amount and preferred denominations (e.g., ‚Çπ100, ‚Çπ500).
	‚Ä¢	The application captures the user‚Äôs current location (latitude, longitude) via device GPS.
	2.	Nearby ATM Search using Ball Tree
	‚Ä¢	A Ball Tree algorithm is applied on ATM location data to quickly identify all ATMs within a 1‚Äì50 km radius.
	‚Ä¢	This ensures spatial efficiency and low-latency search.
	3.	Server Request & Database Access
	‚Ä¢	The filtered ATM IDs are sent to the server, which queries a central ATM database containing:
	‚Ä¢	Real-time or recent cash load data.
	‚Ä¢	Denomination distribution (e.g., ‚Çπ100: 120 notes, ‚Çπ500: 60 notes).
	‚Ä¢	ATM health status (active/inactive, cash-in-transit, etc.).
	4.	Prediction using XGBoost Regression
	‚Ä¢	For each candidate ATM, an XGBoost model is used to predict:
	‚Ä¢	Probability of availability of the requested amount.
	‚Ä¢	Estimated match with the desired denominations.
	‚Ä¢	Features include:
	‚Ä¢	Historical withdrawal patterns (hourly/daily trends).
	‚Ä¢	ATM refill schedules.
	‚Ä¢	Time of day, day of week.
	‚Ä¢	Nearby ATM usage density.
	5.	Probability Calculator & Ranking
	‚Ä¢	The prediction scores are passed to a probability calculator to:
	‚Ä¢	Compute confidence levels.
	‚Ä¢	Rank ATMs based on availability, denomination match, and proximity.
	6.	User Output
	‚Ä¢	The user receives:
	‚Ä¢	A ranked list/map of most likely available ATMs.
	‚Ä¢	Approximate denomination availability.
	‚Ä¢	ETA and distance to each ATM.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ Example Tech Stack
	‚Ä¢	Frontend: React Native / Flutter (for mobile UI + GPS).
	‚Ä¢	Backend: Python (FastAPI / Flask).
	‚Ä¢	Database: PostgreSQL with PostGIS for geospatial queries.
	‚Ä¢	ML Model: XGBoost (regression with custom features).
	‚Ä¢	Geolocation Search: Scikit-learn BallTree or HNSW/FAISS for ANN search.
	‚Ä¢	Deployment: AWS / Azure / GCP.

‚∏ª

