Users currently have no way of knowing the probability of cash and denomination availability in nearby ATMs within a given time frame. Without predictive insights, they are unable to determine whether an ATM will still have their required amount and denominations (e.g., ‚Çπ100, ‚Çπ500) by the time they arrive ‚Äî leading to uncertainty, wasted travel, and poor user experience.

While some existing systems may indicate whether an ATM has money or is operational, they do not provide predictive forecasting of how likely it is that the required amount and denominations will remain available at the user‚Äôs expected arrival time.

üí° What Makes This Invention Unique

This invention uniquely combines real-time geolocation, AI-based regression modeling (e.g., XGBoost), and spatial search (Ball Tree algorithm) to not only identify nearby ATMs, but also to predict the probability of cash and specific denomination availability at a future time (e.g., 30‚Äì45 minutes ahead). Unlike existing solutions that merely indicate if an ATM is operational or has cash, this system provides a forecast‚Äîenabling users to make informed decisions before visiting an ATM. It transforms reactive ATM discovery into a proactive, intelligent experience, minimizing failed visits and optimizing convenience.

üîç Non-Obvious Aspects of the Invention
	1.	Forecasting Cash & Denomination Availability Using AI
Unlike simple status-check systems, this invention uses regression models (e.g., XGBoost) to predict future cash and denomination availability based on time, location, usage patterns, and ATM refill history.
	2.	Time-Sensitive Probability Scoring
It uniquely calculates the probability of availability for a specific future time window (e.g., 30‚Äì45 minutes ahead), rather than just providing static, current ATM status.
	3.	Integration of Ball Tree for Geospatial Filtering
The use of a Ball Tree algorithm to efficiently identify nearby ATMs from the user‚Äôs live GPS location is an intelligent, performance-optimized spatial filtering method‚Äîespecially suitable for real-time use on mobile devices.
	4.	User-Centric Denomination Matching Logic
Most ATM solutions focus only on cash presence; this system adds the ability to match user-specific denomination requests (e.g., ‚Çπ500 only), which is often overlooked in other systems.
	5.	Layered Architecture for Live + Predictive Insights
The design intelligently integrates real-time data (from servers or ATM feeds) with historical trends to deliver live plus forecasted results, a non-trivial combination requiring layered computation.



